EDA on 'Netfix Titles Data'

The goal of this project is to analyze the trends in content by country, year, genre and type.

Dataset: Netflix Shows (Kaggle): https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/infamouscoder/dataset-netflix-shows

Data Cleaning

Let's handle the missing values from the previous missing data observetion.

1. Director, Country & Cast

This columns contain the most NaN values, but instead of deleting them, handle this missing values with 'Unknown' replacement.

In[6]:
columns_to_fill= ['director', 'cast', 'country']

df[columns_to_fill]=df[columns_to_fill].fillna('Unknown')

2. Rating

For the rating column we will fill the missing values with "Not Rated" values.

In[7]:
df['rating']=df['rating'].fillna('Not Rated')

3. Date_added

Date_added column has only 10 missing values so we can just drop them without making any big noise or change in our dataset.

In[8]:
df['date_added']=pd.to_datetime(df['date_added'], errors='coerce')
df=df.dropna(subset=['date_added'])

4. Listed_in

We split the genre (categories) just in case if one gendre contains multiple categories.

In[9]:
df['genre']=df['listed_in'].apply(lambda x: x.split(',')[0])

The movie-duration distribution shows that the amount of the minutes that the most Netflix Movies or TV-Shows have is between 90-110 minutes. according to the highest peak and movie counts, while the other ones are in a lower minutes distribution.

Dashboard

In[45]:
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns

# Load dataset
df = pd.read_csv('Netflix_Show_Dataset.zip', compression='zip')

# Cleaning
df['date_added'] = pd.to_datetime(df['date_added'], errors='coerce')
df = df.dropna(subset=['date_added'])
df[['director','cast','country']] = df[['director','cast','country']].fillna('Unknown')
df['rating'] = df['rating'].fillna('Not Rated')
df['genre'] = df['listed_in'].apply(lambda x: x.split(',')[0])
df['year_added'] = df['date_added'].dt.year
df['duration_int'] = pd.to_numeric(df['duration'].str.extract('(\d+)')[0], errors='coerce')

# KPIs
total_titles = len(df)
total_movies = df[df['type']=='Movie'].shape[0]
total_shows = df[df['type']=='TV Show'].shape[0]
unique_countries = df['country'].nunique()
unique_genres = df['genre'].nunique()

print("Netflix Dataset KPIs")
print(f"Total Titles: {total_titles}")
print(f"Movies: {total_movies}")
print(f"TV Shows: {total_shows}")
print(f"Countries: {unique_countries}")
print(f"Unique Genres: {unique_genres}")

# Dashboard Layout 
plt.figure(figsize=(18,18))

# 1. Movies vs TV Shows
plt.subplot(3,2,1)
sns.countplot(data=df, x='type', palette='pastel')
plt.title("Movies vs TV Shows")

# 2. Content by Release Year
plt.subplot(3,2,2)
sns.countplot(data=df, x='release_year', hue='type', palette='muted')
plt.xticks(rotation=90)
plt.title("Content by Release Year")

# 3. Content by Netflix Added Year
plt.subplot(3,2,3)
sns.countplot(data=df, x='year_added', hue='type', palette='muted')
plt.xticks(rotation=45)
plt.title("Content Added to Netflix by Year")

# 4. Top 10 Countries
plt.subplot(3,2,4)
top_countries = df['country'].value_counts().head(10)
sns.barplot(x=top_countries.values, y=top_countries.index, color='skyblue')
plt.title("Top 10 Content-Producing Countries")

# 5. Top 10 Genres
plt.subplot(3,2,5)
top_genres = df['genre'].value_counts().head(10)
sns.barplot(x=top_genres.values, y=top_genres.index, color='blue')
plt.title("Top 10 Genres")

# 6. Movie Duration Distribution
plt.subplot(3,2,6)
sns.histplot(df[df['type']=='Movie']['duration_int'].dropna(), bins=30, kde=True, color='skyblue')
plt.title("Distribution of Movie Durations")
plt.xlabel("Duration (minutes)")

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

In the dashboard we can observe very clearly what is going on through the Netflix Dataset, for Movies and TV shows. Results show:

  • Movies are more dominant in amount, instead of TV Shows in Netflix.
  • The time of the content released and added to Netflix. Show we comprehend when they were released, added and the amount of users that viewd those movies.
  • Top countries that produce content in Netflix, knowing from where comes from the majority of the contents.
  • The top genres of the Netfix content, meaning that probably there is such amount of content, because people tend to like such genres most.
  • The duration minutes of the Netfix content, what is the ajority duration distribution of the content in Netflix platform.
